Derby Attribute Modifiers
Each derby type modifies the five core attributes of every rooster before a match is simulated.

- Core Attributes:
1. Power
2. Speed
3. Intelligence
4. Accuracy
5. Stamina
These modifiers represent the conditions and fighting style of each derby, encouraging players
to choose breeds strategically.

- Short Heel Derby
The old timer’s favorite
This is a longer, more deliberate derby where power and stamina count more than speed and
intelligence.
Attribute Adjustments
Power: +15%
Speed: −15%
Intelligence: −5%
Accuracy: +5%
Stamina: +10%
Gameplay Effect
Powerful birds thrive here. Matches can be decided quickly with strong bursts of power, or they
may drag out if stamina becomes the deciding factor.

- Pilipino Derby
Fast and furious

This derby heavily favors speed and accuracy.
Attribute Adjustments
Power: −5%
Speed: +20%
Intelligence: +10%
Accuracy: +15%
Stamina: −15%
Gameplay Effect
Speed is the dominant factor. Intelligent birds that are fast and accurate perform extremely well.

- Mexican Derby
Powerful but smart
This derby rewards stamina and accuracy, with a balanced emphasis on strength and calculated
timing.
Attribute Adjustments
Power: +10%
Speed: 0%
Intelligence: +5%
Accuracy: +25%
Stamina: +25%
Gameplay Effect
Birds that combine stamina and accuracy perform best. Strong, durable competitors with good
precision tend to dominate.

- Example Attribute Adjustment

Example Breed: Redquill
Base Attributes:

Power: Average
Speed: High
Intelligence: Medium
Accuracy: High
Stamina: Low
Entered into a Pilipino Derby
Adjusted Attributes:
Power: Slightly Reduced
Speed: Very High
Intelligence: High
Accuracy: Very High
Stamina: Reduced
This system allows the same breed to perform very differently depending on the derby type,
forcing players to make strategic decisions when selecting their entry.

Design Goal
This system ensures that:
• No single breed dominates every derby
• Players must think strategically about which birds to enter
• Each derby type feels unique
• Different play styles are rewarded

If you want to keep building the system logically, the next section we should design is the
match engine, which answers:
How the five attributes actually determine the winner of a match.
That part is where the game becomes mathematically balanced and replayable.